Package gui.ux

Interface Summary
GuiInterface Empty interface that only serves as a marker and designates certain classes as a type of GuiInterface.
 

Class Summary
ConsolePanel Displays any System.out messages sent by any of the GUI agents or engine agents in a JmasterTextArea.
ControlPanel Provides the user with the ability to interact with the Factory simulation.
FactoryPanel Contains the primary focus of the Factory simulation, namely all the Factory components.
KitSelection UI for configuration of the kit and its contents, allows the user to create a custom configuration of parts in a kit for up to eight components.
MainInterface Provides the JFrame in which all other GUI panels will reside and gives the user the ability to interact with said panels and view the board.
NonNormPanel Provides the user with the ability to start non-normative scenarios within the Factory simulation, such as damaging or disabling various parts of the factory.
PowerPanel Provides the user with the ability to enable or disable any GUI agent in the Factory simulation.
UserData Effectively a struct in Java that contains all data that is produced by the UI for use internally within the Factory simulation.
 

Enum Summary
ConsolePanel.Filter Holds all possible filters for the console.
KitSelection.ActionCommand Enum that represents all possible commands for KitSelection.
MainInterface.Status Holds the current state of the MainInterface class.
UserData.Identification Holds all possible identification keys for various panels.
